               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">A. C. WOODWARD</hi>. I come from the General Post-office and pro<lb></lb>duce the originals of certain telegrams which were sent to France last year—the yellow ones are French telegrams, and the blue ones telegrams received in England, to be forwarded to France—I also produce other telegrams under my subpoena—the white ones are inland telegrams—I am asked to produce other telegrams, but under the rules of the office I am not allowed to do so—I have received a warrant from the Home Secretary of State. (<hi rend="italic">The witness was ordered by the Court to produce them, and did so</hi>) I have produced six, they are all dated March, 1877—I have now produced them all.</p>
