                  </hi>. I am a partner in the firm of A. Co<lb></lb>leman and Co., money changers of Cornhill—on 15th November, Murray came and brought two 100<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. Clydesdale notes and six 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. notes which were not Clydesdale—this (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) is one of them—I wrote on it "H. Wells "and wrote in the book "51, Dante Road, Newington Butts," from a piece of paper which he wrote in my presence—I paid him 205<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. I think it was, Bank of England notes which I got from Messrs. Robarts the same morning—I cannot tell what notes they were—but these notes (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) have our stamp on them—I cannot tell you what cheques they came from.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
