                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770409-name-384" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18770409-name-384" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770409-name-384" type="surname" value="COOK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770409-name-384" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES COOK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am one of the rate collectors of St. Martin's-in-the-Fields—I have here a valuation list of the parish, which includes the whole of Charing Cross—there is no such place in the rate-book as Agar Chambers, and I know no such place—there is no Royal Bank of London—there is a large house at the corner of Agar Street which was formerly occupied by the British Bank, it is not the oyal British Bank now, it has been a fire-office for some years.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770409-name-385" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18770409-name-385" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770409-name-385" type="surname" value="RIGGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18770409-name-385" type="given" value="BRINDLEY"></interp>BRINDLEY RIGGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am clerk to Debenham and Storr, the auctioneers—I have known Frederick Kurr for some years, he was a fellow-clerk of mine there—this book (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) is in his writing—he was there from September, 1868, to December, 1874—all these entries are made by him from May, 1869, to April, 1873.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BESLEY</hi>. He was a mere boy when he came—when he left he had 60<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. or 70<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. a year—one of his duties was the checking of the sales—the clerks are well employed from 9.30 to 6 o'clock—he left of his own accord.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770409-name-386" type="witnessName">
